title: ERROR_WINHTTP_AUTO_PROXY_SERVICE_ERROR
msg: Returned by when a proxy for the specified URL cannot be located.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_AUTODETECTION_FAILED
msg: Returned by if WinHTTP was unable to discover the URL of the Proxy Auto-Configuration (PAC) file.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_BAD_AUTO_PROXY_SCRIPT
msg: An error occurred executing the script code in the Proxy Auto-Configuration (PAC) file.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_CANNOT_CALL_AFTER_OPEN
msg: Returned by the object if a specified option cannot be requested after the method has been called.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_CANNOT_CALL_AFTER_SEND
msg: Returned by the object if a requested operation cannot be performed after calling the method.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_CANNOT_CALL_BEFORE_OPEN
msg: Returned by the object if a requested operation cannot be performed before calling the method.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_CANNOT_CALL_BEFORE_SEND
msg: Returned by the object if a requested operation cannot be performed before calling the method.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_CANNOT_CONNECT
msg: Returned if connection to the server failed.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_CHUNKED_ENCODING_HEADER_SIZE_OVERFLOW
msg: Returned by when an overflow condition is encountered in the course of parsing chunked encoding.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_CLIENT_AUTH_CERT_NEEDED
msg:
Returned by when the server requests client authentication.

This error is not supported.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_CONNECTION_ERROR
msg: The connection with the server has been reset or terminated, or an incompatible SSL protocol was encountered. For example, WinHTTP version 5.1 does not support SSL2 unless the client specifically enables it.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_HEADER_ALREADY_EXISTS
msg: Obsolete; no longer used.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_HEADER_COUNT_EXCEEDED
msg: Returned by when a larger number of headers were present in a response than WinHTTP could receive.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_HEADER_NOT_FOUND
msg: The requested header cannot be located.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_HEADER_SIZE_OVERFLOW
msg: Returned by when the size of headers received exceeds the limit for the request handle.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_INCORRECT_HANDLE_STATE
msg: The requested operation cannot be carried out because the handle supplied is not in the correct state.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_INCORRECT_HANDLE_TYPE
msg: The type of handle supplied is incorrect for this operation.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_INTERNAL_ERROR
msg: An internal error has occurred.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_INVALID_OPTION
msg: A request to or specified an invalid option value.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_INVALID_QUERY_REQUEST
msg: Obsolete; no longer used.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_INVALID_SERVER_RESPONSE
msg: The server response cannot be parsed.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_INVALID_URL
msg: The URL is not valid.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_LOGIN_FAILURE
msg: The login attempt failed. When this error is encountered, the request handle should be closed with . A new request handle must be created before retrying the function that originally produced this error.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_NAME_NOT_RESOLVED
msg: The server name cannot be resolved.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_NOT_INITIALIZED
msg: Obsolete; no longer used.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_OPERATION_CANCELLED
msg: The operation was canceled, usually because the handle on which the request was operating was closed before the operation completed.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_OPTION_NOT_SETTABLE
msg: The requested option cannot be set, only queried.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_OUT_OF_HANDLES
msg: Obsolete; no longer used.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_REDIRECT_FAILED
msg: The redirection failed because either the scheme changed or all attempts made to redirect failed (default is five attempts).

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_RESEND_REQUEST
msg: The WinHTTP function failed. The desired function can be retried on the same request handle.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_RESPONSE_DRAIN_OVERFLOW
msg: Returned when an incoming response exceeds an internal WinHTTP size limit.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_SCRIPT_EXECUTION_ERROR
msg: An error was encountered while executing a script.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_SECURE_CERT_CN_INVALID
msg: Returned when a certificate CN name does not match the passed value (equivalent to a error).

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_SECURE_CERT_DATE_INVALID
msg: Indicates that a required certificate is not within its validity period when verifying against the current system clock or the timestamp in the signed file, or that the validity periods of the certification chain do not nest correctly (equivalent to a or a error).

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_SECURE_CERT_REV_FAILED
msg: Indicates that revocation cannot be checked because the revocation server was offline (equivalent to ).

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_SECURE_CERT_REVOKED
msg: Indicates that a certificate has been revoked (equivalent to ).

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_SECURE_CERT_WRONG_USAGE
msg: Indicates that a certificate is not valid for the requested usage (equivalent to ).

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_SECURE_CHANNEL_ERROR
msg: Indicates that an error occurred having to do with a secure channel (equivalent to error codes that begin with "SEC_E_" and "SEC_I_" listed in the "winerror.h" header file).

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_SECURE_FAILURE
msg: One or more errors were found in the Secure Sockets Layer (SSL) certificate sent by the server. To determine what type of error was encountered, check for a notification in a status callback function. For more information, see .

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_SECURE_INVALID_CA
msg: Indicates that a certificate chain was processed, but terminated in a root certificate that is not trusted by the trust provider (equivalent to ).

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_SECURE_INVALID_CERT
msg: Indicates that a certificate is invalid (equivalent to errors such as , , , , , and ).

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_SHUTDOWN
msg: The WinHTTP function support is being shut down or unloaded.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_TIMEOUT
msg:
The request has timed out.

This error can be returned as a result of TCP/IP time-out behavior, regardless of time-out values set in Windows HTTP Services.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_UNABLE_TO_DOWNLOAD_SCRIPT
msg: The PAC file cannot be downloaded. For example, the server referenced by the PAC URL may not have been reachable, or the server returned a 404 NOT FOUND response.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_UNHANDLED_SCRIPT_TYPE
msg: The script type is not supported.

title: ERROR_WINHTTP_UNRECOGNIZED_SCHEME
msg: The URL specified a scheme other than "http:" or "https:".
